Package com.frijolie.cards

Interface Card

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Card>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PlayingCard
    public interface Card
extends java.lang.Comparable<Card>
    Card is an interface representing a playing card in a classic deck of cards. It assumes all cards have a Rank (Ace through King), Suit (Hearts, Clubs, Spades, and Diamonds) and a value. Each card will inevitably need to be compared (ranked) against other similar cards. These cards are intended to be reused in various games that involve a playing card.
    Since:
    0.1
    See Also:
    Rank, Suit

      • hashCode

        int hashCode()
        A method to generate a unique integer value for every card.

        A salt value is added to the ordinal values of Rank and Suit. This value is then multiplied by another salt value to generate the hashcode of a card.
